body:
Hi,

I have a question regarding the `HarfBuzzSharp.Blob.FromStream` implementation, which I pasted here for convenience: 
isn't is necessary to pin the `data` for the whole `Blob` lifetime to avoid memory relocation by the GC?
```
public static unsafe Blob FromStream (Stream stream)
{
	// TODO: check to see if we can avoid the second copy (the ToArray)

	using (var ms = new MemoryStream ()) {
		stream.CopyTo (ms);
		var data = ms.ToArray ();

		fixed (byte* dataPtr = data) {
			return new Blob ((IntPtr)dataPtr, data.Length, MemoryMode.ReadOnly, () => ms.Dispose ());
		}
	}
}
```
